OL,3,CUkrainians mark independence day with
OL,4,Cpoignant Lockerbie ceremony
OL,6,FIn an orchard planted by Ukrainian
OL,7,FPrisoners of War who lived on the site
OL,8,Fin the 1940s, a tree was planted by a
OL,9,Fyoung Ukrainian to mark the day.
OL,10,F"That's quite symbolic," Peter
OL,11,Fexplained.
OL,13,F"The young Ukrainians have come to
OL,14,FScotland and been made welcome.
OL,15,FWhether they stay or they don't stay,
OL,16,Fthey're planting this tree.
OL,18,F"If they come back in a few years
OL,19,Ftime, it will be a day for them to
OL,20,Fremember."
